          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">H placement:</span> ETH puts the 4-point H in play with common tiles (E and T). On a double letter square, H scores 8 alone — making ETH worth 10+ easily.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook plays:</span> ETH hooks forward into ETHS (plural). Back hooks include METH, BETH, and SETH-like patterns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack management:</span> E, T, H are all common tiles. When they appear together without longer options, ETH gives you 6 points and rack turnover.</p>
        </div>
